\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The shadow slipped quietly out the door of the shuttle. It stopped just outside and twisted as if looking around, then darted off toward the rear of the ship. It lingered there for several minutes. Waiting. Watching.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Off in the distance it watched the flashes of light and heard the muffled booms that signaled a firefight of some kind. Nothing it particularly had to worry about, at least not yet.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As it stood there, a breeze came up and whipped its brown robe, violently ripping off its hood to reveal the elongated nose and sharp ears of a Dawgerian. Its looked into the distance, watching a couple of guards as they silently made their way across the tarmac. Its ears twitched as they disappeared around the far corner of a building, and it reached up to replace the hood, covering its face once again in shadow.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Ducking down, it shuffled underneath the rear of the ship and withdrew a small gray box from the folds of its robes. Wires dangled from both sides of the little oblong. The Dawg reached up, the robe falling back off its paw, and tapped a small panel. The panel clicked and suddenly fell off the shuttle. The Dawgerian deftly snatched it out of the air and shook his head, giving a disgusted chuff.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Panel set aside, it recovered a small tool from somewhere else deep within the folds of its robe, and set to cutting and twisting wires, splicing the grey box into the shuttle's circuitry.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Throughout, every few seconds, it would pause to peer about cautiously. After several minutes, it gave a soft growl and began to shove the now-attached gray box into the hole. The panel replaced and sealed, it made it's way out from under the shuttle and off into the shadows, disappearing just a few short steps from where it had exited the ship mere moments ago.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0}